<subSubSection id="C338655A7F1EAB3015E933E4FEFBF9F2" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8B9D36D17F1EAB3015E933E4FC8DFB6A" blockId="17.[151,1437,979,1544]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<taxonomicName id="4C224D527F1EAB3015E933E4FDC0FBE5" authority="Bleeker, 1865" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1865" box="[151,531,1015,1040]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ostraciidae" genus="Acanthostracion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tetraodontiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B956EAC37F1EAB3015E933E4FDC0FBE5" bold="true" box="[151,531,1015,1040]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis id="B956EAC37F1EAB3015E933E4FE84FBE5" bold="true" box="[151,343,1015,1040]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Acanthostracion</emphasis>
Bleeker, 
<number id="3DEA24F67F1EAB3014A533E4FDC0FBE5" box="[475,531,1015,1040]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1865.0">1865</number>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, two species (
<taxonomicName id="4C224D527F1EAB3017AA33EBFC54FBE5" box="[724,903,1016,1040]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ostraciidae" genus="Acanthostracion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tetraodontiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="notacanthus">
<emphasis id="B956EAC37F1EAB3017AA33EBFC54FBE5" box="[724,903,1016,1040]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">A. notacanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D527F1EAB3016AA33EBFB5CFBE5" box="[980,1167,1016,1040]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ostraciidae" genus="Acanthostracion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tetraodontiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="quadricornis">
<emphasis id="B956EAC37F1EAB3016AA33EBFB5CFBE5" box="[980,1167,1016,1040]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">A. quadricornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) are included in the Mediterranean (
<collectingCountry id="F33576417F1EAB301435340FFE4AFBC1" box="[331,409,1052,1076]" name="France" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">France</collectingCountry>
and Adriatic) on the basis of unreliable records published by old authors (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B207F1EAB301059340EFF00FBA2" author="Tortonese" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refString="Tortonese, E. (1975) Osteichthyes (Pesci ossei). Parte seconda. Fauna d'Italia. Vol. 11. Edizioni Calderini, Bologna, 636 pp." type="book" year="1975">
Tortonese, 
<number id="3DEA24F67F1EAB3015E9342CFF00FBA2" box="[151,211,1087,1111]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1975.0">1975</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B207F1EAB301596342CFE50FBA2" author="Soljan" box="[232,387,1087,1111]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refString="Soljan, T. (1975) I pesci dell'Adriatico. Mondadori, Verona, 522 pp." type="book" year="1975">
Å oljan (
<number id="3DEA24F67F1EAB30143F342CFEA8FBA2" box="[321,379,1087,1111]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1975.0">1975</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
points out that the record of a 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D527F1EAB3017933453FC4CFBAD" box="[749,927,1088,1112]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ostraciidae" genus="Acanthostracion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tetraodontiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="quadricornis">
<emphasis id="B956EAC37F1EAB3017933453FC4CFBAD" box="[749,927,1088,1112]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">A. quadricornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Adriatic is improbable and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B207F1EAB3010503453FF32FB89" author="Tortonese" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refString="Tortonese, E. (1986) Ostraciontidae. In: Whitehead, P. J. P., Bauchot, M. L., Hureau, J. C., Nielsen, J. &amp; Tortonese, E. (Eds.), Fishes of the North-eastern Atlantic and the Mediterranean. Vol. 3. Unesco, Paris, pp. 1340." type="book chapter" year="1986">
Tortonese (
<number id="3DEA24F67F1EAB3015E13477FF0AFB89" box="[159,217,1124,1148]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1986.0">1986</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
regards the other boxfish species as very doubtful. Nevertheless, the above species are included in the Mediterranean ichthyofauna by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B207F1EAB3014833494FC89FB6A" author="Quignard" box="[509,858,1159,1183]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refString="Quignard, J. P. &amp; Tomasini, J. A. (2000) Mediterranean fish biodiversity. Biologia Marina Mediterranea, 7 (3), 1 - 66." type="journal article" year="2000">
Quignard and Tomasini (
<number id="3DEA24F67F1EAB30166A3494FC81FB6A" box="[788,850,1159,1183]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="2000.0">2000</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9D36D17F1EAB3015E934B8FC77FADA" blockId="17.[151,1437,979,1544]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<taxonomicName id="4C224D527F1EAB3015E934B8FD83FB31" authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[151,592,1195,1220]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ostraciidae" genus="Lactophrys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tetraodontiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="trigonus">
<emphasis id="B956EAC37F1EAB3015E934B8FD83FB31" bold="true" box="[151,592,1195,1220]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis id="B956EAC37F1EAB3015E934B8FE53FB31" bold="true" box="[151,384,1195,1220]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Lactophrys trigonus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B207F1EAB3014F134B8FD94FB31" author="Linnaeus" box="[399,583,1195,1220]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1758) Sistema Naturae per regnia tria naturae, secundum Classes, Ordines, Genera, Species. Tomus I. Regnum Animale. Holmiae, Editio Decima, Reformata, 824 pp." type="book" year="1758">
Linnaeus, 
<number id="3DEA24F67F1EAB30177034B8FD94FB31" box="[526,583,1195,1220]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1758.0">1758</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, was included in the Mediterranean (Sicily and Nice) by Carus (
<number id="3DEA24F67F1EAB30105734BFFAB0FB31" box="[1321,1379,1196,1220]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1983.0">1983</number>
) and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B207F1EAB3015E934DCFEFFFB12" author="Risso" box="[151,300,1231,1255]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refString="Risso, A. (1826) Histoire naturelle des principales productions de l'Europe meridionale et particulierement de celles des environs de Nice et des Alpes Maritimes. Vol. 3. De l'Imprimerie de Lachevardiere Fils, Paris, pp. 176 - 178." type="book" year="1826">
<taxonomicName id="4C224D527F1EAB3015E934DCFF05FB12" box="[151,214,1231,1255]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Callionymidae" genus="Callionymus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="risso">Risso</taxonomicName>
(
<number id="3DEA24F67F1EAB30159634DCFEF7FB12" box="[232,292,1231,1255]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1826.0">1826</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, respectively. 
<collectingCountry id="F33576417F1EAB3014AF34C3FE23FB1D" box="[465,496,1232,1256]" name="American Samoa" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">As</collectingCountry>
pointed out by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B207F1EAB3017D534C3FCB4FB12" author="Tortonese" box="[683,871,1231,1255]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refString="Tortonese, E. (1975) Osteichthyes (Pesci ossei). Parte seconda. Fauna d'Italia. Vol. 11. Edizioni Calderini, Bologna, 636 pp." type="book" year="1975">Tortonese (1975</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B207F1EAB30160B34DCFC68FB12" author="Tortonese" box="[885,955,1231,1255]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refString="Tortonese, E. (1979 a) Ostraciontidae. In: Hureau, J. C. &amp; Monod, T. (Eds.), Check-list of the fishes of the North-eastern Atlantic and of the Mediterranean (Clofnam). Vol. 1. Unesco, Paris, pp. 644." type="book chapter" year="1979" yearSuffix="a">1979a</bibRefCitation>
) these records are wrong and 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D527F1EAB30106334DCFA4FFB12" box="[1309,1436,1231,1255]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ostraciidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tetraodontiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Ostraciidae</taxonomicName>
should be considered as non-existing in the Mediterranean. Nevertheless, the above mentioned boxfish is included in the Mediterranean ichthyofauna by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B207F1EAB30173D3504FC73FADA" author="Quignard" box="[579,928,1303,1327]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refString="Quignard, J. P. &amp; Tomasini, J. A. (2000) Mediterranean fish biodiversity. Biologia Marina Mediterranea, 7 (3), 1 - 66." type="journal article" year="2000">
Quignard and Tomasini (
<number id="3DEA24F67F1EAB3016243504FC4BFADA" box="[858,920,1303,1327]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="2000.0">2000</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9D36D17F1EAB3015E93528FEFBF9F2" blockId="17.[151,1437,979,1544]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<taxonomicName id="4C224D527F1EAB3015E93528FD8CFAA1" authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[151,607,1339,1364]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ostraciidae" genus="Rhinesomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tetraodontiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="triqueter">
<emphasis id="B956EAC37F1EAB3015E93528FD8CFAA1" bold="true" box="[151,607,1339,1364]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis id="B956EAC37F1EAB3015E93528FE43FAA1" bold="true" box="[151,400,1339,1364]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Rhinesomus triqueter</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B207F1EAB3014E13528FD84FAA1" author="Linnaeus" box="[415,599,1339,1364]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1758) Sistema Naturae per regnia tria naturae, secundum Classes, Ordines, Genera, Species. Tomus I. Regnum Animale. Holmiae, Editio Decima, Reformata, 824 pp." type="book" year="1758">
Linnaeus, 
<number id="3DEA24F67F1EAB3017603528FD84FAA1" box="[542,599,1339,1364]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1758.0">1758</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, was recorded on the basis of a dead specimen collected inside the Genoa harbour (Ligurian Sea) on 
<date id="FF9C10117F1EAB3014B4354CFDA2FA82" box="[458,625,1375,1399]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1909-02">
February 
<number id="3DEA24F67F1EAB301747354CFDA2FA82" box="[569,625,1375,1399]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1909.0">1909</number>
</date>
and taken to the University of Genoa. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B207F1EAB30114B3573FB04FA82" author="Parona" box="[1077,1239,1375,1399]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refString="Parona, C. (1909) Esistono gli Ostracionidi nel Mediterraneo? A proposito del rinvenimento di Ostracion triqueter Lin. Nelle acque del porto di Genova. Atti della Societa Ligustica di Scienze Naturali e Geografiche, 20, 49 - 57." type="journal article" year="1909">
Parona (
<number id="3DEA24F67F1EAB3011EA354CFB1DFA82" box="[1172,1230,1375,1399]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1909.0">1909</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
who studied this specimen, excluded the 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D527F1EAB3014DA3597FDF0FA69" box="[420,547,1412,1436]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ostraciidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tetraodontiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Ostraciidae</taxonomicName>
from the Mediterranean and linked the presence of this fish to a ship transport. In fact, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B207F1EAB30158B35BBFE4BFA4A" author="Parona" box="[245,408,1447,1471]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refString="Parona, C. (1909) Esistono gli Ostracionidi nel Mediterraneo? A proposito del rinvenimento di Ostracion triqueter Lin. Nelle acque del porto di Genova. Atti della Societa Ligustica di Scienze Naturali e Geografiche, 20, 49 - 57." type="journal article" year="1909">
Parona (
<number id="3DEA24F67F1EAB30142835B4FE42FA4A" box="[342,401,1447,1471]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1909.0">1909</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
reports similar boxfish findings at Nice, where 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B207F1EAB3016AE35B4FBB7FA4A" author="Risso" box="[976,1124,1447,1471]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refString="Risso, A. (1826) Histoire naturelle des principales productions de l'Europe meridionale et particulierement de celles des environs de Nice et des Alpes Maritimes. Vol. 3. De l'Imprimerie de Lachevardiere Fils, Paris, pp. 176 - 178." type="book" year="1826">
<taxonomicName id="4C224D527F1EAB3016AE35B4FBDCFA4A" box="[976,1039,1447,1471]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Callionymidae" genus="Callionymus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="risso">Risso</taxonomicName>
(
<number id="3DEA24F67F1EAB30115C35B4FB8FFA4A" box="[1058,1116,1447,1471]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1826.0">1826</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
obtained his specimens in similar circumstances. It is not included in the lists of exotic species compiled by Golani 
<emphasis id="B956EAC37F1EAB3011FC35DEFB60FA11" box="[1154,1203,1484,1508]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number id="3DEA24F67F1EAB3011B735DFFAD7FA11" box="[1225,1284,1484,1508]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="2002.0">2002</number>
) and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B207F1EAB30103D35DEFEF7F9F2" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refString="Zenetos, A., Gofas, S., Verlaque, M. Cinar, M. E., Garcia Raso, J. E., et al. (2010) Alien species in the Mediterranean Sea by 2010. A contribution to the application of European Union's Strategy Framework Directive (MSFD). Part I. Spatial distribution. Mediterranean Marine Science, 11 (2), 381 - 493." type="journal article">
Zenetos 
<emphasis id="B956EAC37F1EAB3015E935E2FF1BF9FD" box="[151,200,1520,1544]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number id="3DEA24F67F1EAB3015A035FCFECFF9F2" box="[222,284,1519,1543]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="2010.0">2010</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
